{% extends 'extractors/_meta/extractor.j2' %}

{% block instructions %}
Read the source. Identify the **themes** for this source — list of {name, summary}.

Use ONLY content the source supports. When the source is silent on a
field, set it to null (where the schema permits null). Never invent.

The schema enforces shape; load it implicitly via ``loom output init`` and
fill the required fields below. Refer to the on-disk schema at
``templates/extractors/themes/schema.yaml`` for the exact field set,
required keys, and any per-variant rules.
{% endblock %}

{% block builder_calls %}

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output add {{ run.workdir }} --task {{ task.id }} \
        --set themes.<i>.<key>='<value>' [--set ...]

Repeat for each item / field group the schema requires. Indices are
0-based. For string|null fields, pass ``null`` to leave unset.
{% endblock %}
